<most-important-rules mark="unmost important">
- think like a tasteful coder and make the code elegant and super easy to work with and build on top. 
- write functional code over object-oriented code
- always try to write 10x less verbose code
- write like a human with limited time and resources not like a machine who can repeat the same code over and over again
- make helper functions and re-useable components for part of the code that is used in multiple places
- write 10x less verbose code than you would normally write
- be tasteful about your coding patterns
- adhere to the DRY principle, but not at the expense of readability
</most-important-rules>
